==English==
===Etymology 1===
From Medieval Latin < Arabic {{ARchar|[[واقع]]}} (''wāqi‘'', [[fall]]ing), from the expression
{{ARchar|[[نسر|النسر]] [[واقع|الواقع]]}} ''(an-nasr al-wāqi‘'', [[fall]]ing [[eagle]]). The active participle {{ARchar|[[واقع]]}} derives from the verb {{ARchar|[[وقع]]}} (''wáqa‘a'', to fall, drop, tumble, alight, pounce).

====Proper noun====
{{wikipedia}}
'''Vega'''

#{{Astronomy}} the brightest [[star]] in the [[constellation]] [[Lyra]].

====Translations====
*Japanese: [[ベガ]] (bega), [[織姫]] (orihime)

===Etymology 2===
From Spanish [[vega]] ([[meadow]], fertile [[lowland]]) < pre-Roman [[w:Iberian language|Iberian]] '''vaica''' or '''baika''' ([[meadow]]) < Iberian '''ibai''' ([[river]]).

====Proper noun====
'''Vega''' (''plural:'' [[Vegas]])

# Hispanic surname and placename, usually preceded by [[la#Spanish|la]] or ''de la'' in the singular, or by [[las#Spanish|las]] or ''de las'' in the plural (e.g., [[Las Vegas]]).


